Territory of Washington, County of Spokane }SS Territory of Washington, Plaintiff Vs Stephen Sterling P. White Defendant } In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Lincoln Judicial District thereof, holding terms at Cheney, Spokane County, in said Territory.
To the Sheriff of Lincoln County, Greeting: IN THE NAME OF THE UNITED STATES, You are hereby commanded to summon Allen Stoakey Franklin Lanud Gentry Perry Harold Alfred Dloaky to be and appear before the District Court aforesaid at the Court House, in Cheney, in said County, on the forthwith day of April A.D. 1885, at - o'clock, - M., to there give evi- dence in the above entitled cause on the part of said Plaintiff Defendant. Witness the Hon. George Turner Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the deal there- of affixed, this 28 day of April A.D. 1885 Kate W. Fraurbach Clerk By R. Strobach Deputy
